No. 106 , on the corner of Piccadilly and Brick Street was built for Hugh Hunlock in 1761 . It was subsequently owned by the 6th Earl of Coventry who remodelled it around 1765 ; most of the architecture from this renovation has survived . In 1869 , it became home to the St James 's Club , a gentleman 's club which stayed there until 1978 . The building is now the London campus of the Limkokwing University of Creative Technology .
